The matrix of various derivatives of J:
∂ρ |K (K is "the point at which we eval")
denotes (is a syntactic stand-in) for either
i the index of a neuron in layer ξ-1, i ∈ {1,...,λ }
j the index of a neuron in layer ξ, j ∈ {1,...,λ }
Matrix dw has the same structure as the weight matrix W
Matrix db has the same structure as the bias matrix b
but w/o assuming sigma() as last activation function
and w/o assuming log-likelihood loss function
Conventions are adapted from those used in the course
"Neural Networks and Deep Learning" by Prof. Andrew Ng.
λ := "the number of neurons in layer l", l ∈ {0,1,2}
